------------------------------------------------------------
12. CHECKPOINT CONCLUSION
------------------------------------------------------------

Galactic turnover radii are organized by a cumulative-stiffness
horizon law rather than by an independent halo profile.

The present checkpoint relation is

    S(R_s) = f_h0 S_tot exp[a (μ_S − μ_S0)]

with

    f_h0 ≈ 0.2
    a    ≈ −0.6

Both numbers arise from the geometry of the universal rotation-curve
mastercurve.

This provides a coherent intermediate result for the galaxy branch of
the MTS cumulative-stiffness framework.

